 fair share of comments that trivialize their skill level for various reasons.\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the time, people who make such slights, assuming they are harmless or claiming they were unintentional, face no consequences.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, when it came to British broadcasterBob Ballard, one casually sexist remark during the swimming competitions got him swiftly removed from his gig.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9907536757617431, \"rank\": 0.00536202723869841, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's#goldfor Australia and a new#Olympicrecordof 3:28,92!\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9875770600757056, \"rank\": 0.00940582731096731, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83c\\udde6\\ud83c\\uddfa  First place in swimming women's 4x100m freestyle relay, which is Australia's 4th gold in a row in the event!\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9875770600757056, \"rank\": 0.00940582731096731, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83c\\udfca@AUSOlympicTeam|@WorldAquatics|#Swimming#Paris2024|#Samsung|#TogetherforTomorrowpic.twitter.com/fKeVI9jDn8  - The Olympic Games (@Olympics)July 27, 2024    During the swimming competition on Saturday, July 27, after the Australian women's 4x100m freestyle relay team won the gold medal, the former BBC reporter commented that the women swimmers were \\\"finishing up\\\" and \\\"you know what women are like\\u2026 hanging around, doing their make-up.\\\"\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999983238333648, \"rank\": 1.5523419460134319e-06, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This remark came at a time when the International Olympic Committee is celebrating Paris 2024 as \\\"The Equal Games,\\\" given that women now make up 50 percent of its participants.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1449, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6521209481145335e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The clip quickly went viral, and while there is no official word on what the Australian swimmers thought of Ballard's remark, Eurosport, Ballard's employer, made their sentiments clear.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.99999832383336